.TH MPF-CLI 1 "June 2026" "MPF" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mpf-cli \- headless orchestrator for redumper, aaru and discimagecreator disc dumps
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mpf-cli
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.IR DRIVE
.IR OUTPUT-DIRECTORY
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mpf-cli
(upstream \fBMPF.CLI\fR) is the headless command-line driver of the
Media Preservation Frontend (MPF) suite. It runs a complete dump
session end-to-end: select a backend dumper, capture all relevant
logs/metadata, post-process the output and write the submission info.

Supported backend dumpers, selected via configuration:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR redumper (1)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR aaru (1)
.IP \(bu 2
.BR discimagecreator (1)
.RE
.PP
The companion validator
.BR mpf-check (1)
is run automatically at the end of the session to produce
\fI!submissionInfo.txt\fR.

When run with no arguments
.B mpf-cli
prints its full help text.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B mpf-cli
loads its configuration from
.IR config.json .
Two locations are checked, in order:
.RS
.IP 1. 3
.I ./config.json
(next to the binary or in the current working directory)
.IP 2. 3
.I ~/.config/mpf/config.json
.RE
.PP
On Fedora the installed binary lives in a system path that is not
user-writable, so the second location is the canonical place to put
your config. If neither path is readable, defaults are used.
.SH SYSTEM-INSTALLED DUMPERS
Unlike the upstream zip the Fedora package does
.B not
ship a bundled \fIPrograms/Creator/\fR folder; the system-installed
.BR redumper (1),
.BR aaru (1)
and
.BR discimagecreator (1)
are resolved via
.BR PATH .
Make sure at least one of them is installed:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo dnf install redumper aaru discimagecreator
.RE
.SH DRIVE ACCESS
.B CAP_SYS_RAWIO
is preset on the shipped binary so vendor SCSI commands work without
sudo. Drive-node access on
.I /dev/sr*
is granted automatically via
.B uaccess
at a local desktop seat; for headless/SSH add yourself to the
.B cdrom
group:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo usermod -aG cdrom $USER
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib64/mpf-cli/MPF.CLI
The actual self-contained .NET binary (cap_sys_rawio=ep).
.TP
.I /usr/bin/mpf-cli
Shell wrapper that exec\(aqs the binary above.
.TP
.I ~/.config/mpf/config.json
User configuration.
.SH NOTES
This manpage is handwritten and tracks upstream MPF
.BR 3.7.1 .
If the upstream tool grows new flags or changes its syntax in a future
release, this page may lag behind the binary; consult
\fImpf-cli --help\fR for the authoritative current option set.
